    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "start"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The latest release of Python is 3.x. As mentioned before, Python is one of the most widely used language over the web. I'm going to list few of them here:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": "left"
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Easy-to-learn"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " − Python has few keywords, simple structure, and a clearly defined syntax. This allows the student to pick up the language quickly."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": "left"
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Easy-to-read"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " − Python code is more clearly defined and visible to the eyes."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": "left"
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Easy-to-maintain"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " − Python's source code is fairly easy-to-maintain."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": "left"
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "A broad standard library"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " − Python's bulk of the library is very portable and cross-platform compatible on UNIX, Windows, and Macintosh."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": "left"
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Interactive Mode"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " − Python has support for an interactive mode which allows interactive testing and debugging of snippets of code."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": "left"
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Portable"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " − Python can run on a wide variety of hardware platforms and has the same interface on all platforms."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": "left"
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Extendable"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " − You can add low-level modules to the Python interpreter. These modules enable programmers to add to or customize their tools to be more efficient."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": "left"
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Databases"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " − Python provides interfaces to all major commercial databases."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": "left"
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "GUI Programming"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " − Python supports GUI applications that can be created and ported to many system calls, libraries and windows systems, such as Windows MFC, Macintosh, and the X Window system of Unix."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
